    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
                <date>May 22<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 1835</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Well my Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee>, I can hardly credit
                my<lb/> senses, that I should have been nearly six months<lb/> in this city without
                receiving a <hi rend="underline">direct</hi> welcome
                <del>from<add>?</add></del><lb/> among my dear family, from one of my most
                valued<lb/> friends, can it be picque or an imaginary slight<lb/> intendency on my
                part, which has withheld the<lb/> desired satisfaction? I have been seemingly<lb/>
                neglectful, yet a prince should consider how<lb/> many circumstances <hi
                    rend="underline">may</hi> prevent a mother of<lb/> almost four <hi
                    rend="underline">infants</hi> and her own health<lb/> never very good, from
                being a punctual correspon<lb/>=dant—I intended to have immediately written<lb/> you
                when I heard of your loss, but really at that<lb/> time some circumstance important
                to my family<lb/> prevented, and I felt my total inability to offer<lb/>
                consolation, when I needed it so much myself<lb/> forgive my friend, all apparent
                neglect I <hi rend="underline">am</hi>
                <hi rend="underline">as</hi><lb/> attached to you as in former times if I know<lb/>
                my own heart, and should be highly pleased to</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>have you a resident among us so that my child<lb/>=ren could be as much
                    <sic>benefitted</sic> by that<lb/> society(<add>the
                        <sic>deprevation</sic><add>?</add> of</add> which has been truly regretted
                by their<lb/> mother) as she has been, I will not <sic>dispair</sic> but<lb/> trust
                my beloved Creator, who has so far listened<lb/> to my prayers, restoring me to my
                dear family w<add>?</add><lb/> Will reunite me with my friends—I cannot<lb/> write
                you a long letter at present as I am<lb/> very busy making my children clothes for
                the<lb/> warm weather, when through I will write<lb/> more fully <sic>untill</sic>
                when believe me<lb/> as ever unalterably your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">A Block</persName>
            </p>
            <p>My love to <persName>Mrs Lyon</persName>, <persName>Allen</persName> &amp;c</p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">attention of Uncle</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName>Rehine</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">W G P —</p>
        </body>
